album.title: Never Be Like You / Smoke & Retribution

wiki.summary: According to Flume, “Never Be Like You” is about a moment in Kai’s life “when everything was going really well and [her] inner saboteur tried to do what she does best.” In the same interview with Triple J, Flume described the creation of the song: Kai and I were sending ideas back and forth online, then met up in NYC and went into the studio. We laid down some chords and started an idea but weren’t feeling inspired. So we went out into the night for a few hours and when we returned, it all started to come together. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: According to Flume, “Never Be Like You” is about a moment in Kai’s life “when everything was going really well and [her] inner saboteur tried to do what she does best.” In the same interview with Triple J, Flume described the creation of the song: Kai and I were sending ideas back and forth online, then met up in NYC and went into the studio. We laid down some chords and started an idea but weren’t feeling inspired. So we went out into the night for a few hours and when we returned, it all started to come together. The first single from Flume’s sophomore album Skin, “Never Be Like You” is also his first song to reach number one in his home country of Australia. Flume’s described Skin as “headphone music,” a departure from the “festival music” that helped him make a name for himself. Read more on Last.fm.
